## Adding a New Contact

1. Navigate to the relevant segment (Influencers, White Label, or NAD Dealers)
2. Click the **+ Add** button in the top right of the table
3. Fill in the contact details — the form adapts based on contact type:
   - Influencers: name, category, platform, score, Instagram, website
   - White Label / NAD Dealers: company, tier, HQ, website, contact email
4. Set an initial Pipeline Status (defaults to Prospect)
5. Click **Add Contact**

The new contact saves to the Google Sheet and appears in the table immediately.

---

## Exporting Contacts

Each segment table has an **⬇ Export** button that downloads the current view as a `.csv` file — including pipeline status, last notes, and next actions.

The **All Contacts** (Pipeline) view has an **⬇ Export All** button that exports every contact across all three segments in one file.

Exported files are named with today's date, e.g. `HNT-Influencers-2026-06-18.csv`. You can open them in Excel or Google Sheets.

---

## The Google Sheet

The CRM reads from and writes to the **HNT-CRM Master** Google Sheet. You can open it directly to:
- View all contacts in spreadsheet format
- Bulk edit multiple contacts at once
- Filter or sort using Google Sheets tools

Any changes made directly in the Sheet will appear in the CRM the next time you reload the page.

**CRM tracking columns in the Sheet:**
- Pipeline Status
- Next Action
- Next Action Date
- Assigned Rep
- Last Contacted Date
- Last Contact Notes
- Date Added

